CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 30, 1958, pg. 1, reads: "Grieved Over Mother's Death, Marion Moone, 36, Commits Suicide! Coroner Investigates - The front porch railing where the short belt, looped around the bannister, formed a noose from which the body of Marion Edward Moone hung about five feet from the ground, is being investigated by a coroner's deputy. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Coroner's deputy standing on stairs to porch of home at 2528 Wadsworth Terrace, Hill District
